The US amends the rules for obtaining a visa
Before consulting the service providers, persons must present themselves to the visa application service before they have been consulted, which means that waiting times will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and in the consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants have to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, initial letters in English) prior to their consultation in the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the Consulate prior to the discussion.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment agreement, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is delivered.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterpart to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visas do not have to have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to imagine at the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consultation in the consulate remain there for less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service surcharge of $26.
Additional information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
